It was a Tuesday night, the kind of night where time feels irrelevant. I had just gotten home, showered, and collapsed into bed after taking forever to dry my hair. The hum of my fan was on full blast, and the city outside felt like it belonged to someone else.

My phone buzzed. I ignored it.

I rolled over and stared at the microwave clock across the room.

11:11.

“Cute,” I whispered to no one.

Angel numbers again. The universe had been throwing them at me like darts: 111, 444, 333. Like it had a crush on me.

But what? My rent was late. My fridge was a joke. My energy was in the red.

The silence got deeper.

“BOOP. Got your nose!” I imagined the universe saying.

I laughed out loud.

Then cried.

Then laughed again.

I reached for my phone and texted myself:

